<p><i><b>The Once and Future King</b></i> is an <a href="/wiki/Arthurian" title="Arthurian" class="mw-redirect">Arthurian</a> <a href="/wiki/Fantasy" title="Fantasy">fantasy</a> novel written by <a href="/wiki/T._H._White" title="T. H. White">T. H. White</a>. It was first published in 1958 and is mostly a composite of earlier works.</p>
<p>The title comes from the supposed inscription of the marker over <a href="/wiki/King_Arthur" title="King Arthur">King Arthur's</a> grave: <i>HIC IACET ARTHURUS REX QUONDAM REXQVE FUTURUS</i> — "Here lies Arthur, the once and future king."</p>
